  <refsect1 id='description'>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      <command>ipsec</command> invokes any of several utilities
      involved in controlling the IPsec encryption/authentication
      system, running the specified <replaceable>command</replaceable>
      with the specified <replaceable>argument</replaceable> as if it
      had been invoked directly.  This largely eliminates possible
      name collisions with other software, and also permits some
      centralized services.
    </para>
    <para>
      <userinput>ipsec help</userinput> lists the available commands.
      Most have their own manual pages.
    </para>
    <para>
      <userinput>ipsec version</userinput> outputs the software version.
    </para>
    <para>
      <userinput>ipsec directory</userinput> reports where the
      <command>ipsec</command> sub-commands are stored.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1 id='commands'>
    <title>COMMANDS</title>
    <para>
      To get a list of supported commands, use the command
      <command>ipsec --help</command>.  The full set of commands are
      listed below:
    </para>

    <variablelist>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec start</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec stop</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec restart</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to control the <command>pluto</command> daemon using
	    the host init system. Supported init systems are sysv,
	    systemd, upstart and openrc.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec barf</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to dumps the internal system status to stdout for
	    debugging.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec add</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec up</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec start</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec route</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec ondemand</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec down</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec delete</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to manually add, remove, up or down connections.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec whack</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to communicate direct commands to the pluto daemon
	    using the whack interface.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec initnss</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to initialise the NSS database that contains all the
	    X.509 certificate information and private RSA keys
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec checknss</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to check the NSS database and initialize it when it
	    is not present and optionally set trust bits for CA
	    certificates.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec import</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to import PKCS#12 X.509 files into the NSS database
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec checkconfig</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to validate ipsec configuration (default
	    @@IPSEC_CONF@@).
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec checknflog</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to initialise rules for the nflog devices when
	    specified via the nflog= or nflog-all= configuration
	    options.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec stopnflog</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to delete iptables rules for the nflog devices.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry>
	<term>
	  <citerefentry><refentrytitle><command>ipsec trafficstatus</command></refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry>
	</term>
	<listitem>
	  <para>
	    Used to get tunnel traffic status.
	  </para>
	</listitem>
      </varlistentry>

    </variablelist>

  </refsect1>

  <refsect1 id='returncode'><title>RETURN CODE</title>
  <para>
    The ipsec command passes the return code of the sub-command
    back to the caller. The only exception is when
    <userinput>ipsec pluto</userinput> is used without --nofork,
    as it will fork into the background and the ipsec command returns
    success while the pluto daemon may in fact exit with an error code
    after the fork.
  </para>
</refsect1>

